Package Controller

Class AppointmentOutcomeController

java.lang.Object
Controller.AppointmentOutcomeController
public class AppointmentOutcomeController extends Object
The AppointmentOutcomeController class is responsible for managing appointment outcomes. This includes creating, updating, and retrieving appointment outcomes for doctors and patients.

  • Method Details

    • createAppointmentOutcome

      public void createAppointmentOutcome(String date, String time, String typeOfService, ArrayList<PrescribedMedication> medications, String notes, String doctorID, String patientID, String appointmentID)
      Creates a new appointment outcome and saves it in the system. If an appointment ID is provided, updates the appointment status to "completed".
      Parameters:
      date - the date of the appointment outcome
      time - the time of the appointment outcome
      typeOfService - the type of service provided
      medications - a list of prescribed medications
      notes - consultation notes
      doctorID - the doctor's ID
      patientID - the patient's ID
      appointmentID - the appointment ID (can be "-" if not linked to an appointment)

    • getAppointmentOutcomeByAppointmentID

      public AppointmentOutcome getAppointmentOutcomeByAppointmentID(String appointmentId)
      Retrieves the appointment outcome based on the appointment ID.
      Parameters:
      appointmentId - The ID of the appointment to retrieve the outcome for.
      Returns:
      The appointment outcome corresponding to the given appointment ID, or null if no match is found. This method iterates through all appointment outcomes and returns the one that matches the specified appointment ID.

    • setPrescribedMedicineUpdatedStatus

      public void setPrescribedMedicineUpdatedStatus(String appointmentOutcomeId, ArrayList<PrescribedMedication> newMedications)
      Updates the prescribed medications for a specific appointment outcome.
      Parameters:
      appointmentOutcomeId - The ID of the appointment outcome to update.
      newMedications - A list of new prescribed medications to set for the appointment outcome. This method retrieves the appointment outcome using the specified ID, updates the prescribed medications, and saves the updated outcome back to the data source.
